\begin_layout Standard
The compressible Euler equations can be conditionally averaged in order
 to divide the atmsophere into partitions based on, for example, the presence
 of buoyant updrafts, stable air and downdraughts.
 These three partitions are labelled using 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

.
 Each partition has separate prognostic variables but all regions share
 the same pressure.
 This partitioned atmosphere is composed of a number of species indexed
 by label 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

 (for example air, 
\begin_inset Formula $s=a$
\end_inset

, and water, 
\begin_inset Formula $s=w$
\end_inset

) and each species can be in a gaseous (
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

), liquid (
\begin_inset Formula $\ell$
\end_inset

) or solid (ice) phases:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
i=\begin{cases}
0 & \text{ stable}\\
1 & \text{ updraught}\\
2 & \text{ downdraught, }
\end{cases} & s=\begin{cases}
a & \text{ air}\\
w & \text{ water, }
\end{cases} & \text{phase}=\begin{cases}
g & \text{ gaseous}\\
\ell & \text{ liquid}.\\
\text{ice} & \text{ solid}
\end{cases}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

Assuming that the atmosphere consists of a mixture of perfect gases and
 incompressible liquids (no ice), the conditionally averaged Euler equations
 for a moist atmosphere can be approximated as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{\partial\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\mathbf{u}_{i}}{\partial t}+\nabla\cdot\left(\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\mathbf{u}_{i}\mathbf{u}_{i}\right) & = & -2\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\boldsymbol{\Omega}\times\mathbf{u}_{i}-\sigma_{i}\nabla p+\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\mathbf{g}\label{eq:condMom}\\
 & + & \sum_{j\ne i}\left(\sigma_{j}\rho_{j}\mathbf{u}_{j}S_{ji}-\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\mathbf{u}_{i}S_{ij}-\sigma_{i}\sigma_{j}\mathbf{d}_{ij}\right)\nonumber \\
\frac{\partial\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}}{\partial t}+\nabla\cdot(\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\mathbf{u}_{i}) & = & \sum_{j\ne i}\left(\sigma_{j}\rho_{j}S_{ji}-\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}S_{ij}\right)\label{eq:condCont}\\
\frac{\partial\sigma_{i}\rho_{gis}}{\partial t}+\nabla\cdot(\sigma_{i}\rho_{gis}\mathbf{u}_{i}) & = & -\sigma_{i}C_{is}\label{eq:condGas}\\
 & + & \sum_{j\ne i}\left(\sigma_{j}\rho_{gjs}S_{ji}-\sigma_{i}\rho_{gis}S_{ij}\right)\nonumber \\
\frac{\partial\sigma_{i}v_{\ell is}}{\partial t}+\nabla\cdot\left(\sigma_{i}v_{\ell is}\mathbf{u}_{i}\right) & = & \sigma_{i}C_{is}\label{eq:condLiq}\\
 & + & \sum_{j\ne i}\left(\sigma_{j}v_{\ell js}S_{ji}-\sigma_{i}v_{\ell is}S_{ij}\right)\nonumber \\
\frac{\partial\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\theta_{i}}{\partial t}+\nabla\cdot\left(\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\mathbf{u}_{i}\theta_{i}\right) & = & \sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\theta_{i}Q_{i}\label{eq:condTheta}\\
 & + & \sum_{j\ne i}\left(\sigma_{j}\rho_{j}\theta_{j}S_{ji}-\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}\theta_{i}S_{ij}-\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}H_{ij}\right)\nonumber 
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

with the global equation of state and the equation of state for each partition:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
p_{0}\Pi^{\frac{1-\kappa}{\kappa}} & = & \frac{\rho R_{t}\theta}{1-v_{\ell}}=\sum_{i}\sigma_{i}\rho_{i}R_{ti}\theta_{i}\label{eq:condState}\\
p_{0}\Pi^{\frac{1-\kappa}{\kappa}} & = & \frac{\rho_{i}R_{ti}\theta_{i}}{1-v_{\ell i}}\label{eq:condStatei}
\end{eqnarray}

